J. E. BARON, as Trustee in Bankruptcy of George Bernard Morris, Appellant, v. BANK OF AMERICA NATIONAL TRUST & SAVINGS ASSOCIATION, Appellee. No. 7180. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 5, 1933. Irl D. Brett, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Freston & Files, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and GARRECHT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for the respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal in above cause dismissed without costs to either party; mandate forthwith.
